Article 1. Definitions

1.1 "Software" means ProtoCloack2 and all components included in an official
binary release package, including but not limited to the server and client
executables, installation scripts, systemd units, sysctl configuration,
configuration templates, documentation, checksum files, and related materials.

1.2 "User" means any individual or legal entity that obtains, installs,
deploys, runs, redistributes, or otherwise uses the Software.

1.3 "Operator" means a User that deploys, hosts, operates, or manages the
Software for itself, customers, third-party miners, or other end users.

1.4 "End Miner" means any third party whose mining device, hashrate, or
Stratum connection is forwarded, proxied, protected, or otherwise handled
through an instance of the Software operated by an Operator.

1.5 "Official Release" means a Software release package, binary executable,
checksum, release note, or document made available by the copyright holder
through its designated official release channel, including GitHub Releases or
another official publication location.

1.6 "Official Repository" means the repository, release page, or publication
channel designated by the copyright holder for official information, public
binary releases, checksums, security notices, and documentation. The copyright
holder may change the Official Repository or official release channel by
publishing an official notice or a new Official Release.

1.7 "Unmodified Release Package" means a release package, archive, installer,
or binary executable whose contents are byte-for-byte identical to the
corresponding Official Release. Mirroring, storing, renaming, transmitting,
adding external checksum files, or adding external digital signatures does not
constitute modification if the released files themselves are not changed.
Changing executables, scripts, configuration templates, documentation, license
text, or any other released file constitutes modification.

1.8 "Source Code" means human-readable source files, private build materials,
private tests, private configuration, private key material, unpublished
documentation, and any other materials not included in an Official Release.

1.9 "Software Fee" means any fee charged to a third party for the Software
itself, including license fees, download fees, delivery fees, resale fees,
rental fees, access fees, or any arrangement requiring payment to obtain,
receive, or use the Software. Service Charges, the Service Fee, and User Fees
are not Software Fees.

1.10 "Service Charges" means fees charged by a User or Operator for
value-added services around the Software, including installation, deployment,
configuration, integration, operations, hosting, monitoring, training,
technical support, or mining proxy services.

1.11 "Service Fee" or "SVC" means the built-in fee mechanism of the Software
that supports ongoing development, maintenance, release, and licensed use of
the Software. Unless the copyright holder specifies a different rate through an
Official Release, remote configuration, per-instance configuration, or written
authorization, the default Service Fee rate is 0.5%. The Service Fee may be
implemented by routing part of the mining work, shares, or submit flow
scheduled by the Software to a wallet, pool, or account controlled by the
copyright holder or its designee. Because of pool difficulty, network
conditions, rejection rate, randomized scheduling, and runtime environment
differences, the actual accepted-share ratio may statistically vary around the
configured rate.

1.12 "User Fee" means an optional fee mechanism configured by the Operator and
directed to a wallet, pool, or account designated by the Operator. The Operator
sets, discloses, and bears all compliance responsibility for User Fees.

1.13 "Public Fee Statistics Endpoint" means the public read-only fee
statistics interface provided by the Software for End Miners or third-party
verifiers, including but not limited to the fee-stats interface on default TCP
port 9100, or an equivalent interface later specified in official
documentation.

1.14 "Based on the Software" means directly or indirectly using the Software
or any portion of it, including binaries, configuration, documentation,
protocol behavior, non-public materials, or information obtained through
reverse engineering, to copy, modify, adapt, translate, create derivative
works, combine, or implement the same or substantially similar functionality.
Independent development from scratch without copying the Software, using
non-public materials of the Software, or using information obtained through
reverse engineering of the Software is not "Based on the Software".

1.15 "Applicable Law" means the laws and regulations in force in the relevant
jurisdiction.

Article 2. Release Model and Fees

2.1 The Software is released under a proprietary, binary-only model. This
Agreement grants no right to obtain, use, copy, modify, redistribute, or demand
Source Code.

2.2 Users may obtain Official Release binary packages free of upfront charge.
No party may charge any Software Fee to any third party.

2.3 The Service Fee is a material part of the licensed-use and maintenance
model of the Software. By installing, running, deploying, or otherwise using
the Software, the User acknowledges and agrees to the Service Fee mechanism.

2.4 This Agreement does not prohibit Users or Operators from providing services
to third parties and charging Service Charges. Service Charges must not be
marketed, bundled, disguised, or charged as Software Fees.

2.5 Operators may configure User Fees, subject to the disclosure obligations
in Article 6 and Applicable Law.

Article 3. Grant of Rights

Subject to continuous compliance with this Agreement, the copyright holder
