Article 11. Termination

11.1 If the User breaches any term of this Agreement, this Agreement shall not
terminate immediately. The User is granted a 30-day grace period to cure such
breach. The grace period shall be calculated from the date the User becomes
aware, or reasonably should have become aware, of the breach.

11.2 If the breach involves circumvention of the Service Fee, tampering with
fee statistics, maliciously misleading End Miners, unlawful use, unauthorized
modification, or unauthorized distribution of modified versions, the copyright
holder may require the User to stop the relevant conduct immediately; such
immediate stop requirement does not affect the 30-day cure period for other
curable matters.

11.3 If, after the grace period expires, the User fails to cure the breach, is
unable to cure it, or refuses to cure it, the copyright holder may revoke the
license granted under this Agreement, and this Agreement shall terminate upon
expiry of the grace period.

11.4 Upon termination, the User must immediately cease using the Software and,
within a reasonable time and using reasonable efforts, delete, destroy, or
render unusable all copies of the Software under the User's control, including
copies made for distribution. For backup copies created automatically as part
of the User's normal backup processes that cannot reasonably be individually
identified or immediately deleted, the User may retain such backup copies for
the ordinary backup retention period, provided that the User does not restore,
use, or re-distribute them, and deletes or overwrites them upon expiry of the
retention period or when feasible.

11.5 Articles 4, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, and 12 shall survive termination of this
Agreement.

